@startuml
title Java Worker - Redis Consumer & Job Processing

participant "Redis Queue" as Redis
participant "Redis Listener" as Listener
participant "Scan Processor" as Processor
participant "Scanner Orchestrator" as Orchestrator
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

== Worker Startup ==

Listener -> Listener: 1. @PostConstruct
Listener -> Redis: 2. Subscribe to 'scan:queue'
Listener -> Listener: 3. BRPOP scan:queue (blocking)

== Job Reception ==

Redis --> Listener: 4. Job received
Listener -> Processor: 5. process(scan_job)

Processor -> DB: 6. UPDATE scans SET status='processing'
Processor -> Processor: 7. Start metrics timer

== Execute Scans ==

Processor -> Orchestrator: 8. executeScans(domain)
Orchestrator -> Orchestrator: 9. Run 5 parallel scanners

note right of Orchestrator
  Parallel execution:
  - DnsScanner
  - SslScanner
  - HttpScanner
  - CtLogScanner
  - ExposureScanner
end note

Orchestrator --> Processor: 10. Return AggregatedResult

== Store & Process ==

Processor -> DB: 11. UPDATE scans SET raw_results
Processor -> Processor: 12. Call OpenAI API
Processor -> DB: 13. UPDATE scans SET status='completed', score
Processor -> DB: 14. INSERT INTO findings

Processor -> Processor: 15. Log completion
Processor -> Listener: 16. Return to listening

@enduml